	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Galveston</placeName> <date>Jany. 20<hi rend="sup">Th</hi> 1855</date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><date>Saturday</date> Night</p>
				<p>My esteemed friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I avail myself of the earliest<lb/> opportunity to express my sincere acknow&#45;<lb/>ledgements for the very kind notice you<lb/> have taken of my melancholy request con&#45;<lb/>veyed in the few lines I addressed you<lb/> <date>Nov. 15th</date>.  The <date>Jany</date>. Number of the &#8220;Occident&#8221;<lb/> arrived to&#45;day&#44; wherein my dear sister and self<lb/> read with deep emotion the very <hi rend="underline">appropriate</hi><lb/> and <hi rend="underline">feeling tribute</hi> you have paid to the mem&#45;<lb/>ory of our loved departed ones.  It elicited<lb/> feelings of gratitude towards you that I<lb/> would willingly convey to paper&#44; but I<lb/> know that I could not do justice to you&#44; or<lb/> myself in attempting to express them.<lb/>  I must therefore beg you kind friend&#44; to<lb/> receive my assurance&#44; that <hi rend="underline">we both</hi> entertain<lb/> sentiments of high regard for you&#44; and<lb/> shall never be unmindful of the strong<lb/> and satisfactory proof you have given us</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>of your friendly consideration.  In all<lb/> probability&#44; with God&#39;s will&#44; we will<lb/> shortly be in your city&#44; when I trust<lb/> to be enabled to express in stronger terms<lb/> how much we appreciate the favor confer&#45;<lb/>red.  Hoping that you derived ben&#45;<lb/>efit from your western tour&#44; and that<lb/> these few lines will find you in the<lb/> enjoyment of health&#44; with the combined<lb/> regards of my beloved sister&#44; and<lb/> brother&#45;in&#45;law&#44; I remain dear sir<lb/> your sincerely obliged friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Hannah Dyer</persName></hi></p>
		</body>
